%spark.pyspark

import os
from datetime import datetime
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from pyspark.sql import SQLContext

from pyspark.sql.types import StructType, StructField, StringType, IntegerType
import pyspark.sql.functions as F
from pyspark.sql.window import Window
from pyspark import StorageLevel

%spark.pyspark

ACCESS_KEY = os.environ['AWS_ID']
SECRET_KEY = os.environ['AWS_SECRET']

sc._jsc.hadoopConfiguration().set("fs.s3n.awsAccessKeyId", ACCESS_KEY)
sc._jsc.hadoopConfiguration().set("fs.s3n.awsSecretAccessKey", SECRET_KEY)

sq = SQLContext(sc)

dailyPath = "s3n://sierra-leone-lake/blob/AGGREGATED_CDRS/africell/summaries/user_queries-daily"
weeklyPath = "s3n://sierra-leone-lake/blob/AGGREGATED_CDRS/africell/summaries/user_queries-weekly"
hourlyPath = "s3n://sierra-leone-lake/blob/AGGREGATED_CDRS/africell/summaries/user_queries-hourly"
dailyPatternPath = "s3n://sierra-leone-lake/blob/AGGREGATED_CDRS/africell/summaries/user_queries-daily-avg"
districtQueriesPath = "s3n://sierra-leone-lake/blob/AGGREGATED_CDRS/africell/summaries/district_queries"

%spark.pyspark
names={'antenna_id': StringType(),'time': StringType(),'cdr_type': StringType(),'source': StringType(),'target': StringType(),'duration': IntegerType()}
fields=[]
for header in names:
    fields.append(StructField(header, names[header], False))
schema = StructType(fields)
# df = sq.read.csv('./data/20200321_20.csv', schema=schema)
df = sq.read.csv('s3n://sierra-leone-lake/blob/cdrs/africell-raw/2020030[3-9]_[0-2]0.csv', schema=schema)
# df = sq.read.csv('s3n://sierra-leone-lake/blob/cdrs/africell-raw/2020*.csv', schema=schema)

df = df.withColumn('direction', F.lower(F.split(df['cdr_type'], ' ').getItem(0)))\
        .withColumn('subscriber', F.col('source'))\
        .withColumn("call_datetime", F.to_timestamp("time"))\
        .withColumn("call_date", F.to_date("call_datetime"))\
        .withColumn("week", F.weekofyear("call_date"))\
        .withColumn("hour", F.hour("call_datetime"))\
        .withColumn("site", F.expr("substring(antenna_id, 1, length(antenna_id)-1)"))
df = df.drop('time', 'cdr_type', 'source', 'target', 'direction', 'antenna_id')

%spark.pyspark
district = Window.partitionBy('admin2Name', 'call_date')
        # .groupBy('admin2name', 'subscriber')\
        # .agg(F.avg('count').alias('count'))\
joined = df\
        .join(towers, df.site==towers.site_id)\
        .groupBy('admin2Name', 'subscriber', 'call_date')\
        .agg(F.count('call_date').alias('count'))\
        .withColumn('bin', bin(F.col('count')))\
        .groupBy('call_date', 'admin2Name', 'bin')\
        .agg(F.count('subscriber').alias('users'))\
        .withColumn('sort', F.split(F.col('bin'), '-').getItem(0).cast(IntegerType()))\
        .orderBy('admin2Name', 'call_date', 'sort')
relative_freq = joined\
        .withColumn('total', F.sum('users').over(district))\
        .withColumn('relative', F.col('users')/F.col('total'))
relative_freq.createOrReplaceTempView("relative_freq")

%spark.pyspark

# daily = df.groupBy('subscriber', 'call_date').agg(F.count('call_date').alias('count'))
# daily.persist(StorageLevel.MEMORY_AND_DISK)

# weekly = daily\
#         .withColumn("week", F.weekofyear("call_date"))\
#         .groupBy('subscriber', 'week')\
#         .agg(F.sum('count').alias('count'))

# hourly = df.groupBy('subscriber', 'hour', 'call_date').agg(F.count('hour').alias('count')).groupBy('hour').agg(F.avg('count').alias('count'))
daily_pattern = df.groupBy('subscriber', 'call_date', 'hour')\
            .agg(F.count('call_date').alias('count'))\
            .groupBy('call_date', 'hour')\
            .agg(F.count('subscriber').alias('users'), F.avg('count').alias('per_user'))\
            .orderBy('call_date', 'hour')
duration = df.where(F.col('duration')>0)\
            .groupBy('subscriber', 'call_date', 'hour')\
            .agg(F.avg('duration').alias('avg_duration'))
duration_bins = duration\
            .withColumn('bin', bin(F.col('avg_duration')))\
            .groupBy('bin')\
            .agg(F.count('avg_duration').alias('numUsers'))\
            .withColumn('sort', split(F.col('bin'), '-').getItem(0).cast(IntegerType()))\
            .orderBy('sort')
duration_pattern = duration\
            .groupBy('call_date', 'hour')\
            .agg(F.avg('avg_duration').alias('avg_duration'))
duration_bins.createOrReplaceTempView("duration_bins")
